        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 8 at 6:58PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>Scattered rain showers will affect areas along the Highway 2
corridor from Shelby to Harlem this evening, along with areas
further south around Loma and Fort Benton as well. Some of the
rain showers will produce strong wind gusts of 45 to 55 mph as
well. The rain showers will be brief, with rainfall amounts of
0.05 inches to about 0.15 inches possible.
</description>
